        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Deuteronomy 4:40",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " having been prefixed later? So Graf, Kue., Wellh., König, etc. Or is the appearance of the heading just here compatible with the theory that the whole of 1–26 is the work of one author? So Dillm. and Driver on the ground that a new title would not be unnatural where the actual exposition of the law at last begins (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Deuteronomy 1:6",
        "children": []
      },
      {
